# .trivyignore — vulnerability waivers for the Trivy CI security scan.
#
# GOVERNANCE (ADR-021): once the scan enforces (Phase 2, exit-code 1), a
# committed entry here is the ONLY way a vulnerability stops failing the build.
# Every entry is a deliberate, reviewed decision to accept a specific risk —
# treat additions as a security decision, not a config tweak.
#
# Each waiver MUST carry, as comments directly above the ID:
#   - the CVE / advisory ID + the affected package and version
#   - WHY it is accepted (unfixable upstream / not reachable / false positive …)
#   - WHO reviewed it, and a review-by date to force re-evaluation
#
# Format: one advisory ID per line (e.g. CVE-2025-12345).
# Docs: https://trivy.dev/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#by-finding-ids
#
# No waivers yet — the dependency tree is expected clean. Add entries only with
# the justification block above.
